WEBVTT

00:10.144 --> 00:12.580
- * ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:12.613 --> 00:13.581
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:13.614 --> 00:21.555
*

00:35.436 --> 00:38.206
- * CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:38.239 --> 00:46.214
*

00:46.247 --> 00:48.682
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:48.716 --> 00:50.184
*

00:50.218 --> 00:52.486
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:52.520 --> 00:53.554
*

00:53.587 --> 00:56.757
* CUE THE PULSE TO BEGIN

00:59.227 --> 01:02.196
[jazzy blues music]

01:02.230 --> 01:10.204
*

02:16.270 --> 02:19.273
- NICE NIGHT FOR A RIDE.

02:19.307 --> 02:21.242
- WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

02:21.275 --> 02:22.910
- FOLLOWING YOU,
TO SEE WHERE YOU'VE BEEN GOING

02:22.943 --> 02:25.779
FOR THE LAST THREE WEEKS.

02:25.813 --> 02:27.681
- NOW YOU KNOW.

02:27.715 --> 02:30.284
AND NOW YOU CAN GO BACK HOME
AND GO TO BED.

02:31.552 --> 02:33.554
- DO YOU KNOW WHAT TIME IT IS?

02:33.587 --> 02:36.524
- THE LITTLE HAND'S ON THE TWO,
THE BIG HAND'S ON THE THREE.

02:36.557 --> 02:37.858
QUARTER AFTER TWO?

02:37.891 --> 02:40.428
- WHY THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING THIS?

02:40.461 --> 02:43.297
- 'CAUSE I'VE GOT
TO GET IN SHAPE.

02:43.331 --> 02:45.533
- FOR WHAT?
- THE LIBERTY RIDE.

02:45.566 --> 02:46.934
- YOU'RE NOT
STILL THINKING OF GOING.

02:46.967 --> 02:48.536
- JUST BECAUSE YOU
AND THE REST OF THEM

02:48.569 --> 02:50.938
DISQUALIFIED ME
DOESN'T MEAN THAT I DID.

02:50.971 --> 02:53.674
- WE'RE JUST CONCERNED.

02:53.707 --> 02:55.943
- THERE'S SO MANY
POOR STARVING CHILDREN

02:55.976 --> 02:57.945
WHO GO TO BED HUNGRY
EVERY NIGHT.

02:57.978 --> 02:59.713
BE CONCERNED ABOUT THEM.

02:59.747 --> 03:01.482
- SO WHY THE SECRECY?

03:01.515 --> 03:02.883
- BECAUSE I DON'T WANT
PEOPLE LIKE YOU SAYING,

03:02.916 --> 03:05.586
"YOU CAN'T,
YOU MUSTN'T."

03:05.619 --> 03:07.755
I DON'T WANT EVERY CUNTY FAGGOT
WHO GOES TO THE GYM

03:07.788 --> 03:11.725
SAYING, "POOR KINNEY.
TOLD YOU SO."

03:11.759 --> 03:13.427
- I HAVE TO HAND IT TO YOU,

03:13.461 --> 03:16.864
YOUR PERSEVERANCE IS SURPASSED
ONLY BY YOUR NARCISSISM.

03:16.897 --> 03:21.335
- AND THERE YOU HAVE IT,
THE SECRET TO MY SUCCESS.

03:21.369 --> 03:24.305
UNLESS...I'M PROVEN WRONG
BY THE NAYSAYERS,

03:24.338 --> 03:26.374
AND I FAIL DISMALLY.

03:26.407 --> 03:29.310
- OH, YOU'RE NOT GOING TO FAIL,
DISMALLY OR OTHERWISE.

03:29.343 --> 03:32.880
YOU'RE GOING TO BE A BIG, FAT,
FUCKING SUCCESS, AS ALWAYS.

03:32.913 --> 03:34.982
WE'RE GOING TO GO
ON THE RIDE TOGETHER,

03:35.015 --> 03:39.453
AND AT NIGHT,
WE'LL PITCH A TENT...

03:39.487 --> 03:44.525
AND WE'LL HAVE HOT,
PASSIONATE SEX UNDER THE STARS.

03:48.429 --> 03:50.731
- WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOING?

03:50.764 --> 03:52.500
- I'VE HEARD THAT,
WHEN ACHIEVING YOUR GOAL,

03:52.533 --> 03:55.303
IT'S BEST TO VISUALIZE IT.

04:01.909 --> 04:04.878
[rock music]

04:04.912 --> 04:07.748
*

04:07.781 --> 04:10.351
* WHITE LIGHTNING

04:10.384 --> 04:12.653
* OH, WHITE LIGHTNING

04:12.686 --> 04:14.622
*

04:14.655 --> 04:16.790
* WHITE LIGHTNING

04:16.824 --> 04:19.893
[panting]

04:19.927 --> 04:21.429
- AND FIVE MORE SECONDS.

04:21.462 --> 04:23.664
COME ON!
PUSH IT, ALL YOU GOT.

04:23.697 --> 04:27.067
THREE, TWO, ONE.

04:27.100 --> 04:29.903
AND SIT.
[all sighing in relief]

04:29.937 --> 04:32.940
TWO MINUTE COOLDOWN.
- [groans]

04:32.973 --> 04:34.808
I'D SAY WE'RE IN GREAT SHAPE
FOR THE RIDE, WOULDN'T YOU?

04:34.842 --> 04:36.710
- PROVIDED MY ASS HOLDS OUT.

04:36.744 --> 04:38.579
- I'VE NEVER KNOWN IT TO FAIL.

04:38.612 --> 04:40.448
- YOU'VE NEVER RIDDEN IT
FOR 350 MILES.

04:40.481 --> 04:41.782
- MAYBE YOU COULD
GET AN EXTENDED WARRANTY

04:41.815 --> 04:43.584
SINCE IT'S NO LONGER NEW.

04:43.617 --> 04:45.986
- A DEEP-FAT-FRIED
VICTORY DINNER SAYS

04:46.019 --> 04:48.789
YOU'LL BE SEEING IT CROSS
THE FINISH LINE AHEAD OF YOURS.

04:48.822 --> 04:52.826
- THIS ISN'T A RACE.
ANYONE WHO RIDES IS A WINNER.

04:52.860 --> 04:55.062
- HEY, THERE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
SOME REALLY HOT GUYS RIDING.

04:55.095 --> 04:56.664
- THAT'S WHAT I HEARD.

04:56.697 --> 04:59.400
- A FRIEND OF MINE WENT ON
A RIDE LAST YEAR.

04:59.433 --> 05:00.968
HE SAID AT NIGHT,
THE SHOWERS GET REALLY STEAMY,

05:01.001 --> 05:02.936
AND HE WASN'T TALKING
ABOUT THE WATER.

05:02.970 --> 05:04.738
- BRINGING ANYTHING WITH YOU
THAT STARTS WITH A "C"?

05:04.772 --> 05:06.840
- YOU MEAN MY VITAMINS?
YOU KNOW ME.

05:06.874 --> 05:08.842
NEVER LEAVE HOME WITHOUT THEM.

05:08.876 --> 05:12.413
[both laugh]

05:12.446 --> 05:15.416
- WE'RE GIVING THE RIDERS A BIG
SEND-OFF BEFORE THEY LEAVE.

05:15.449 --> 05:17.551
I'VE PREPARED
A SPEECH EXPRESSING

05:17.585 --> 05:19.753
THE CENTER'S GRATITUDE.
- AH.

05:19.787 --> 05:21.622
- A BANNER, A BAND,
DRAG QUEEN CHEERLEADERS.

05:21.655 --> 05:24.758
- OH, SOUNDS GREAT.
I WISH I COULD BE THERE.

05:24.792 --> 05:26.494
- OH, US TOO,

05:26.527 --> 05:28.896
CONSIDERING ALL THE WORK
YOU'VE DONE.

05:28.929 --> 05:30.964
- I'M NOT SUPPOSED
TO LEAVE MY GODDAMN BED.

05:30.998 --> 05:33.033
DOCTOR'S ORDERS.
- IF IT WERE ME,

05:33.066 --> 05:35.102
I'D BE GOING STIR-CRAZY.
- NOT ME.

05:35.135 --> 05:38.105
I'D FLUFF UP MY PILLOWS,
EAT BONBONS, AND WATCH OPRAH.

05:38.138 --> 05:40.574
- HEY, CAN I GET ANYONE
A DRINK?

05:40.608 --> 05:43.110
- THANKS, LINZ.
WE WERE JUST LEAVING.

05:43.143 --> 05:45.613
- NOW, REMEMBER
WHAT THE DOCTOR SAID

05:45.646 --> 05:50.017
AND STAY PUT.

05:50.050 --> 05:53.053
BYE.

05:53.086 --> 05:54.988
[door closes]

05:55.022 --> 05:56.624
- THINK I'LL TAKE GUS
TO THE PARK.

05:56.657 --> 05:58.492
HE COULD USE SOME FRESH AIR
AND SO COULD I.

05:58.526 --> 05:59.860
- I KNOW THE FEELING.

05:59.893 --> 06:02.630
- WILL YOU BE ALL RIGHT?
- FINE, THANK YOU.

06:02.663 --> 06:05.065
OH, BEFORE YOU GO,
COULD YOU BRING ME SOME TEA?

06:05.098 --> 06:09.503
AND MAYBE SOME PEACH YOGURT
AND A COUPLE OF COOKIES.

06:09.537 --> 06:11.739
AND GO UPSTAIRS
AND GET ME MY MAROON CARDIGAN?

06:11.772 --> 06:14.408
I'M A LITTLE CHILLY.
- ANYTHING ELSE?

06:14.442 --> 06:17.010
- ANOTHER BLANKET
AND A FIRMER PILLOW.

06:17.044 --> 06:19.613
AND AS LONG AS YOU'RE OUT,
I NEED A ROLL OF STAMPS,

06:19.647 --> 06:21.915
AS WELL AS THESE THINGS
FROM THE PHARMACY.

06:25.819 --> 06:27.621
[scoffs]
I'M NOT ALLOWED TO MOVE.

06:27.655 --> 06:28.922
WHAT THE HELL ELSE
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

06:28.956 --> 06:30.491
- YOU MIGHT TRY SAYING PLEASE,

06:30.524 --> 06:31.925
AND STOP TREATING ME
LIKE THE HIRED HELP,

06:31.959 --> 06:32.926
WHICH ACTUALLY
WOULDN'T BE SO BAD.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.428
AT LEAST I'D GET PAID.

06:34.462 --> 06:36.163
- SORRY,
BUT IT'S YOUR CHILD TOO.

06:36.196 --> 06:38.632
- THAT STILL DOESN'T GIVE YOU
THE RIGHT TO ORDER ME AROUND.

06:38.666 --> 06:40.501
- I WASN'T ORDERING YOU.

06:40.534 --> 06:42.703
YOU HAVE A HELL OF A NERVE
TALKING TO ME ABOUT RIGHTS.

06:42.736 --> 06:45.439
YOU HAD NO RIGHT TO...
- OKAY.

06:45.473 --> 06:46.907
OKAY.

06:46.940 --> 06:48.642
I'LL DO ANYTHING YOU WANT,

06:48.676 --> 06:53.847
BUT LET'S STOP THIS, RIGHT NOW.

06:57.951 --> 06:59.186
- WELL, BEFORE THEY GIVE US
THE GREEN LIGHT,

06:59.219 --> 07:00.988
THEY WANT TO SEE
WHAT THEY'RE BUYING,

07:01.021 --> 07:02.923
AND HOW MUCH
IT'S GOING TO COST THEM,

07:02.956 --> 07:05.859
WHICH WILL BE PLENTY
BY THE TIME I'M THROUGH.

07:05.893 --> 07:07.561
SO I'D LIKE ONE OF YOU
TO BE HERE

07:07.595 --> 07:08.929
TO HELP ME CONVINCE THEM WHY

07:08.962 --> 07:10.864
WE HAVE TO BE TRUE
TO THE ORIGINAL VISION.

07:10.898 --> 07:12.833
- SURE, BRETT,
WHICH ONE OF US DO YOU WANT?

07:12.866 --> 07:15.469
- PROBABLY JUSTIN.
UH, NO OFFENSE, MIKE.

07:15.503 --> 07:18.071
THE STUDIO EXECS UNDERSTAND
PICTURES MORE THAN WORDS.

07:18.105 --> 07:20.207
- WHATEVER'S GOOD
FOR THE PROJECT.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.543
- JUSTIN?
- WHEN WOULD IT HAPPEN?

07:22.576 --> 07:26.013
- THIS THURSDAY.
- WHAT ABOUT THE LIBERTY RIDE?

07:26.046 --> 07:27.815
- I CAN'T HEAR YOU.
YOU'RE BREAKING UP.

07:27.848 --> 07:29.583
- NOTHING, BRETT.
HE'LL BE THERE.

07:29.617 --> 07:31.885
- GREAT, I'LL HAVE MY ASSISTANT
SEND YOU AN E-TICKET.

07:31.919 --> 07:33.854
YOU CAN STAY IN MY GUEST HOUSE.
[phone beeps]

07:33.887 --> 07:34.888
THAT'S MY OTHER LINE.

07:34.922 --> 07:36.624
GOT TO GO.

07:36.657 --> 07:37.958
- CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?
YOU'RE GOING TO L.A.

07:37.991 --> 07:39.760
- BUT I MADE A COMMITMENT.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.563
I HAVE SPONSORS, I RAISED MONEY.
- IF THE MOVIE GETS MADE,

07:42.596 --> 07:43.997
YOU CAN GIVE THEM
A MILLION BUCKS.

07:44.031 --> 07:45.899
HEY, CARL.

07:45.933 --> 07:48.135
YOU LOOKING FOR SOME SUPERHEROES
TO HELP YOU FIGHT CRIME?

07:48.168 --> 07:51.872
- ACTUALLY, I'M LOOKING FOR YOU.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.974
WILL YOU EXCUSE US, JUSTIN?

07:54.007 --> 07:55.876
- YEAH, SURE.

07:55.909 --> 07:57.010
SEE YA.

07:57.044 --> 07:59.980
- BUY SOME SUN BLOCK.

08:00.013 --> 08:01.849
MIND IF I EAT MY LUNCH
WHILE YOU INTERROGATE ME?

08:01.882 --> 08:04.852
- BE MY GUEST.

08:04.885 --> 08:06.987
- YOU WANT SOME?
- NO, THANKS.

08:07.020 --> 08:09.723
MY STOMACH'S BEEN ACTING
A LITTLE FUNNY.

08:09.757 --> 08:10.791
- SOMETHING WRONG?

08:10.824 --> 08:12.860
- IT'S YOUR MOTHER.

08:12.893 --> 08:14.595
- I REALIZE SHE CAN BE
A LITTLE SPICY,

08:14.628 --> 08:16.263
BUT I'VE NEVER KNOWN HER
TO CAUSE INDIGESTION.

08:16.296 --> 08:19.667
- AS YOU KNOW, WE'VE BEEN
SEEING EACH OTHER A LOT LATELY.

08:19.700 --> 08:21.268
- I KNOW.
I THINK IT'S GREAT.

08:21.301 --> 08:24.271
- BUT IT CAN'T GO ON THIS WAY.

08:24.304 --> 08:26.740
- SUDDENLY I'M NOT FEELING
SO GOOD MYSELF.

08:26.774 --> 08:28.676
- NAH, IT'S NOTHING LIKE THAT.

08:28.709 --> 08:31.011
WHAT I'M TRYING TO SAY IS,
I NEED SOMEONE IN MY LIFE

08:31.044 --> 08:33.647
WHO'LL MAKE ME LAUGH,
WHO'LL MAKE ME FEEL GOOD.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.883
- I'M ALREADY TAKEN, CARL.

08:35.916 --> 08:39.219
- THAT'S WHY I WANT TO MARRY
YOUR MOTHER.

08:42.055 --> 08:44.992
AS SOON AS YOU SAY "YOU MAY,"
I WANT HER TO SAY "I DO."

08:49.597 --> 08:51.732
- THAT'S...
THAT'S A BIG REQUEST.

08:54.001 --> 08:55.636
NORMALLY I ASK
FOR PERSONAL REFERENCES

08:55.669 --> 08:57.905
AND W-2 FORMS
FOR THE LAST THREE YEARS

08:57.938 --> 09:01.108
AND AN ARREST REPORT.

09:01.141 --> 09:05.078
BUT IN YOUR CASE,
I ONLY HAVE ONE QUESTION.

09:11.218 --> 09:13.787
DO YOU PROMISE...

09:13.821 --> 09:15.923
YOU'LL BE GOOD TO HER?

09:15.956 --> 09:18.692
- I GIVE YOU MY WORD.

09:21.629 --> 09:25.098
- THEN THE ANSWER IS,
YOU MAY.

09:27.835 --> 09:30.203
- I'M LIKE
HER EMOTIONAL PUNCHING BAG.

09:30.237 --> 09:31.705
SHE POUNDS AWAY AT ME ALL DAY,

09:31.739 --> 09:33.807
AND I JUST STAND THERE
AND TAKE IT.

09:33.841 --> 09:36.610
- THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE
OLD KILLER MULDOON TO ME.

09:36.644 --> 09:39.212
- I HAVE NO CHOICE. HER DOCTOR
SAID SHE HAS TO STAY IN BED.

09:39.246 --> 09:42.015
NO STRESS.
- OH.

09:42.049 --> 09:43.884
SO NOW YOU HAVE
TO SERVE IN SILENCE

09:43.917 --> 09:46.086
LIKE THAT MUNCHER IN
THE MILITARY, GRETA CAMEMBERT.

09:46.119 --> 09:47.888
- MARGARETHE CAMMERMEYER,

09:47.921 --> 09:49.957
AND I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
LONGER I CAN PUT UP WITH IT.

09:49.990 --> 09:52.693
- WELL...
THEN DON'T.

09:52.726 --> 09:56.396
- BUT IT'S MY FAULT.
I'M THE ONE TO BLAME.

09:56.429 --> 09:58.866
- SO THEREFORE
YOU'RE BEATING YOURSELF UP.

09:58.899 --> 10:01.101
OR RATHER, LETTING MELANIE
DO IT FOR YOU.

10:01.134 --> 10:03.303
- OLD-FASHIONED
AS IT MAY SEEM,

10:03.336 --> 10:06.106
I STILL BELIEVE IN LOYALTY,
NOT BETRAYAL,

10:06.139 --> 10:08.842
SELF-CONTROL,
NOT SELF-INDULGENCE,

10:08.876 --> 10:11.011
EVEN IF I FAILED TO LIVE UP
TO MY OWN EXPECTATIONS.

10:11.044 --> 10:13.380
- TELL HER THAT.
- SHE REFUSES TO LISTEN.

10:13.413 --> 10:16.383
SHE THINKS BECAUSE I FUCKED SAM
THAT I'M NO LONGER A LESBIAN.

10:16.416 --> 10:18.318
- WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT A STICKLER
FOR DETAIL SHE IS.

10:18.351 --> 10:19.386
- BRIAN, PLEASE.

10:19.419 --> 10:22.389
- WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

10:22.422 --> 10:24.391
IF IT'S OVER,
GET THE HELL OUT.

10:24.424 --> 10:27.661
- IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

10:27.695 --> 10:30.263
WHAT ABOUT GUS?
AND THE ONE ON THE WAY?

10:30.297 --> 10:32.265
- STAYING TOGETHER FOR THE SAKE
OF THE CHILDREN

10:32.299 --> 10:35.202
IS A FUCKING POOR EXCUSE.

10:35.235 --> 10:38.906
I PROUDLY OFFER MYSELF
AS EXHIBIT A.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.843
HEY, SONNY BOY.
COME HERE.

10:46.046 --> 10:51.284
- UNDIES, SWEATERS.

10:51.318 --> 10:52.886
COULD YOU HOLD THESE FOR ME
FOR A MINUTE?

10:52.920 --> 10:55.155
THANKS, HONEY.
- UH, DEBBIE, I-I...

10:55.188 --> 10:57.691
- CARL, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO SAY IT.

10:57.725 --> 10:59.426
I-I KNOW WE WERE SUPPOSED TO
BE GOING TO ST. PETE'S

10:59.459 --> 11:01.228
FOR A FEW DAYS, BUT...

11:01.261 --> 11:03.296
HELL, THIS IS...
THE RIDE'S FOR THE HOSPICE.

11:03.330 --> 11:06.033
HOW COULD I NOT DO MY BIT
AND VOLUNTEER?

11:06.066 --> 11:07.935
- YOU GOT A BIG HEART.
THAT'S WHY I LOVE YOU.

11:07.968 --> 11:10.237
- BESIDES, IT'LL STILL BE THERE.
WE'LL GO ON OUR HONEYMOON.

11:10.270 --> 11:12.172
- WHAT?
- HA! I'M JOKING.

11:12.205 --> 11:15.709
HONEYMOON? US?

11:15.743 --> 11:18.445
OKAY, SO, UM, OH.
[clears throat]

11:18.478 --> 11:21.782
SO YOU, UH, YOU WANTED
TO TELL ME SOMETHING.

11:21.815 --> 11:23.450
GO AHEAD, I'M ALL EARS.

11:23.483 --> 11:26.319
- DEBBIE, HONEY...
- EARS. FUCK!

11:26.353 --> 11:28.722
I NEED EARMUFFS.

11:28.756 --> 11:34.327
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE COLDER
THAN A WITCH'S TIT IN CANADA.

11:34.361 --> 11:36.363
UH, SO GO AHEAD, HONEY,

11:36.396 --> 11:39.199
WHAT IS IT YOU WANTED TO SAY?

11:39.232 --> 11:41.234
- BE SURE TO BUNDLE UP.

11:41.268 --> 11:44.104
[doorbell chimes]

11:44.137 --> 11:45.472
- KEEP PACKING, DEB, OR...

11:45.505 --> 11:46.807
WHATEVER IT IS
YOU'RE DOING IN THERE.

11:46.840 --> 11:47.975
I'LL GET IT.

11:54.514 --> 11:55.482
TEDDY.
- HEY, EM.

11:55.515 --> 11:56.483
I HAVE SOMETHING FOR YOU.

11:56.516 --> 11:58.351
- SO WHERE IS HE?

11:58.385 --> 12:01.855
- UH, SORRY, NOTHING LIKE THAT.
IT'S JUST, UH, THIS.

12:01.889 --> 12:03.757
IT'S THE $5,000 I OWE YOU
FOR COVERING FOR ME

12:03.791 --> 12:07.527
THAT TIME I "BORROWED" FROM
GUS' COLLEGE FUND.

12:07.560 --> 12:10.363
- I, UH...
THANK YOU, TEDDY.

12:10.397 --> 12:12.165
- I'M SURE YOU CAN USE IT.

12:12.199 --> 12:14.367
- I DON'T MEAN FOR THAT.

12:14.401 --> 12:16.103
I MEAN FOR KEEPING YOUR WORD.

12:16.136 --> 12:17.971
FOLLOWING THROUGH. HMM.

12:18.005 --> 12:19.973
YOU'VE COME A LONG WAY.

12:20.007 --> 12:22.509
- YEAH, I GUESS I HAVE.

12:22.542 --> 12:24.177
- AND NOW YOU'RE ABOUT TO GO
EVEN FURTHER, HUH?

12:24.211 --> 12:25.779
THIS TIME ON A BIKE?

12:25.813 --> 12:28.381
- UH, ACTUALLY, I'VE, UH,
CHANGED MY MIND.

12:28.415 --> 12:30.117
I'M NOT GOING.

12:30.150 --> 12:31.919
- WHAT?

12:31.952 --> 12:34.321
- YEAH, I'M UP TO MY GARBANZOS
IN WORK.

12:34.354 --> 12:35.856
I CAN'T LEAVE BRIAN
WITH EVERYTHING.

12:35.889 --> 12:37.791
A-AND I JUST GOT
THESE NEW PLANTS,

12:37.825 --> 12:39.559
AND THEY'RE AT
THAT CRITICAL PHASE

12:39.592 --> 12:42.062
WHERE IF YOU DON'T WATCH THEM,
THEY COULD GO INTO SHOCK, SO.

12:42.095 --> 12:44.531
- I'M THE ONE WHO'S IN SHOCK.
YOU'VE BEEN TRAINING FOR WEEKS.

12:44.564 --> 12:46.533
- IT'S ONLY A BIKE RIDE.

12:46.566 --> 12:49.536
BESIDES, I'VE GOT
MY MEETINGS, MY GROUPS.

12:49.569 --> 12:51.271
- CAN'T YOU SKIP THEM
FOR A FEW DAYS?

12:51.304 --> 12:53.006
- [sighs]
WELL, THEY'RE WHAT'S GOTTEN ME

12:53.040 --> 12:54.474
THROUGH THESE PAST FEW MONTHS.

12:54.507 --> 12:55.909
I MEAN, THEY'VE BEEN
MY SUPPORT SYSTEM.

12:55.943 --> 12:58.578
BUT ON THE RIDE,
I'D BE ON MY OWN.

12:58.611 --> 13:00.313
I MEAN, SAY THERE'S A TRIGGER,

13:00.347 --> 13:02.916
THAT I SEE GUYS DOING DRUGS,
THAT I'M TEMPTED,

13:02.950 --> 13:05.552
WHERE CAN I GO?
WHO CAN I CALL?

13:05.585 --> 13:07.020
I CAN'T TAKE A CHANCE
OF THAT HAPPENING,

13:07.054 --> 13:09.489
OF BECOMING THAT PERSON AGAIN.

13:09.522 --> 13:12.459
THAT'S ENOUGH.

13:15.963 --> 13:17.297
[door closes]

13:17.330 --> 13:20.467
- GEARS LUBED UP,
SEAT NICE AND TIGHT.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.469
- I'M GOING TO RIDE IT,
NOT FUCK IT.

13:24.938 --> 13:26.907
- WOW!

13:26.940 --> 13:29.076
THAT IS ONE COOL BIKE.

13:29.109 --> 13:31.044
- YEAH. HUNTER NEEDED A NEW ONE
FOR THE LIBERTY RIDE.

13:31.078 --> 13:33.580
- CAN I TAKE IT OUT FOR A SPIN?
PLEASE, DAD, PLEASE.

13:33.613 --> 13:35.215
- SURE, SON.

13:35.248 --> 13:36.950
- JUST DON'T BE LATE FOR DINNER.

13:36.984 --> 13:39.953
I'M MAKING YOUR FAVORITE,
BLUEBERRY CRUMBLE.

13:44.624 --> 13:48.061
- SO, HOW WERE THINGS
AT WORK, DEAR?

13:48.095 --> 13:50.463
- LET'S SEE. HMM.

13:50.497 --> 13:51.464
I FINISHED
THE LATEST ADVENTURE OF RAGE.

13:51.498 --> 13:53.100
- HEY.

13:53.133 --> 13:56.003
- MADE 600 BUCKS IN SALES
ON THE WEBSITE.

13:56.036 --> 13:57.504
- HMM.

13:57.537 --> 14:00.507
- OH, AND CARL HORVATH
WANTS TO MARRY MY MOTHER.

14:03.243 --> 14:04.644
- WHAT?

14:04.677 --> 14:09.616
- HE ACTUALLY ASKED ME
FOR HER HAND.

14:09.649 --> 14:12.252
- DID YOU GIVE IT TO HIM?

14:12.285 --> 14:13.653
- EVERY LAST DIGIT.

14:13.686 --> 14:15.989
AFTER ALL,
THAT'S WHAT TWO PEOPLE DO

14:16.023 --> 14:18.425
WHEN THEY LOVE EACH OTHER,
RIGHT, GET MARRIED?

14:31.271 --> 14:33.106
- WHAT THE FUCK'S ALL THIS?

14:33.140 --> 14:35.642
- JUST MAKING SURE WE HAVE
EVERYTHING WE NEED FOR THE RIDE.

14:35.675 --> 14:40.147
TENT, SLEEPING BAGS, FIRST AID
KIT, TOOL KIT, RAIN GEAR,

14:40.180 --> 14:42.682
TWO SETS OF WARM CLOTHES,
ONE DILDO.

14:42.715 --> 14:45.018
- YOU CERTAINLY THOUGHT
OF EVERYTHING.

14:45.052 --> 14:48.121
BUT WHY DO YOU NEED A TENT

14:48.155 --> 14:49.689
IF YOU'RE GOING TO BE STAYING
IN A MANSION?

14:49.722 --> 14:52.525
HMM?

14:52.559 --> 14:54.661
MICHAEL TOLD ME YOU'RE WINGING
TO THE COAST TOMORROW

14:54.694 --> 14:56.029
TO HUDDLE WITH STUDIO HEADS.

14:56.063 --> 14:58.131
- I NEVER SAID I WAS GOING.

14:58.165 --> 14:59.666
- HE SEEMS TO THINK
THAT YOU ARE.

14:59.699 --> 15:01.368
- WELL, I'M NOT.

15:01.401 --> 15:05.305
WE'RE GOING ON THE RIDE
TOGETHER, AS PLANNED.

15:05.338 --> 15:09.176
- WELL, UNFORTUNATELY THERE'S
BEEN A SLIGHT CHANGE OF PLANS.

15:09.209 --> 15:10.677
I'M NOT GOING.

15:10.710 --> 15:12.412
- WHY THE FUCK NOT?

15:12.445 --> 15:14.447
- BECAUSE YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:14.481 --> 15:16.349
I'M NOT IN GOOD ENOUGH SHAPE.

15:16.383 --> 15:18.151
- I SAW YOU CYCLING.

15:18.185 --> 15:20.020
- YEAH, AND AFTER 30 MILES,
I WAS WINDED.

15:20.053 --> 15:21.488
ON THE RIDE WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO DO

15:21.521 --> 15:24.491
80 TO 100 MILES A DAY,
MAYBE MORE.

15:24.524 --> 15:26.159
THERE'S NO WAY I CAN MAKE IT.

15:26.193 --> 15:27.727
- THAT IS BULLSHIT.
YOU'RE JUST SAYING THAT

15:27.760 --> 15:30.230
TO GET ME TO GO TO HOLLYWOOD.

15:30.263 --> 15:32.599
- THEN GO ON THE RIDE
WITHOUT ME.

15:32.632 --> 15:35.202
SACRIFICE YOUR FUTURE.

15:35.235 --> 15:39.973
NOW, THAT'S WHAT I CALL
CHARITY.

15:40.007 --> 15:41.941
[water running]

15:44.344 --> 15:47.314
- NOW HERE'S
MY CELL PHONE NUMBER.

15:47.347 --> 15:51.318
AND HERE'S BEN'S CELL PHONE
NUMBER.

15:51.351 --> 15:55.488
HERE'S HUNTER'S
CELL PHONE NUMBER.

15:55.522 --> 15:59.492
AND HERE'S THE NUMBER
FOR OUR HOTEL IN TORONTO.

15:59.526 --> 16:04.131
- CHRIST, I'LL BE TOO BUSY
CALLING YOU TO GIVE BIRTH.

16:04.164 --> 16:05.598
- YOU KNOW,
MAYBE I SHOULDN'T GO.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.534
- MICHAEL, THE BABY'S
NOT DUE FOR WEEKS.

16:07.567 --> 16:10.003
- IN CASE SOMETHING HAPPENS...
- NOTHING'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

16:10.037 --> 16:12.105
BELIEVE ME, I'LL BE
SCREAMING FROM BOREDOM

16:12.139 --> 16:13.340
LONG BEFORE I'LL BE
SCREAMING FROM LABOR.

16:13.373 --> 16:14.741
- SO GO AND HAVE A GOOD TIME.

16:14.774 --> 16:16.609
IT'LL BE AN AMAZING ADVENTURE.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.611
- I JUST WISH I COULD BE THERE
TO SEE YOU GUYS OFF.

16:18.645 --> 16:22.349
- YOU STAY RIGHT HERE.

16:22.382 --> 16:25.752
AND REMEMBER, IF YOU NEED
TO GET AHOLD OF ME...

16:25.785 --> 16:28.021
- WE KNOW, MICHAEL.
WE KNOW.

16:35.295 --> 16:37.230
- NOW WOULD YOU GET
THE FUCK OUT OF HERE?

16:37.264 --> 16:40.267
- WE LOVE YOU.
- WE LOVE YOU.

16:40.300 --> 16:43.636
- WHAT A LUCKY KID...

16:43.670 --> 16:47.407
TO BE COMING INTO
SUCH A WARM AND LOVING HOME.

16:53.813 --> 16:56.716
[door opens and closes]

17:08.295 --> 17:11.531
- 50 TUNA SANDWICHES,
50 HAM AND CHEESE,

17:11.564 --> 17:14.534
50 CHICKEN SALAD,
50 ROAST BEEF.

17:14.567 --> 17:16.703
- OH, ROAST BEEF'S
TEDDY'S FAVORITE.

17:16.736 --> 17:18.471
BETTER MAKE THAT 49.

17:18.505 --> 17:20.607
- IT'S A DAMN SHAME
HE DECIDED NOT TO GO.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.409
WOULD'VE BEEN GOOD FOR HIM.
GIVEN HIM A VICTORY.

17:22.442 --> 17:24.144
SOME SELF-ESTEEM.

17:24.177 --> 17:27.614
- HE'S TOO AFRAID TO LEAVE
HIS MEETINGS AND GROUPS,

17:27.647 --> 17:30.183
YOU KNOW, THAT WITHOUT
HIS SUPPORT SYSTEM, HE'LL SLIP.

17:30.217 --> 17:32.719
HE'S AS ADDICTED TO THEM
AS HE WAS TO THE CRYSTAL METH.

17:32.752 --> 17:35.422
- WELL, AT LEAST IT'S
A HEALTHY ADDICTION, HUH?

17:35.455 --> 17:37.657
TOO BAD HE CAN'T TAKE
HIS SUPPORT SYSTEM WITH HIM.

17:40.360 --> 17:42.195
HEY, CARL.

17:42.229 --> 17:43.430
HONEY, HI.

17:43.463 --> 17:45.298
CAN I INTEREST YOU
IN A BOX LUNCH?

17:45.332 --> 17:48.601
IT'S FOR THE BUS TRIP TO
TORONTO, BUT I GOT AN EXTRA.

17:48.635 --> 17:50.570
- THANKS, I--
UH, I ALREADY ATE.

17:50.603 --> 17:52.239
- WELL, YOU WANT TO LEND A HAND?
EM...

17:52.272 --> 17:53.506
GIVE CARL SOME FRUIT.
SHOW HIM HOW IT'S DONE.

17:53.540 --> 17:55.775
- YOU TAKE AN APPLE
OR AN ORANGE.

17:55.808 --> 17:59.179
YOU DROP IT INTO THE BOX
COMME CA.

17:59.212 --> 18:01.381
THEN YOU MOVE ON TO THE NEXT.
GOT IT?

18:01.414 --> 18:02.882
- THANKS FOR THE TRAINING.

18:02.915 --> 18:04.651
DEB, COULD YOU STOP
FOR A SECOND? HONEY...

18:04.684 --> 18:06.519
- CARL, I'M UP TO MY ASS
IN HARD-BOILED EGGS.

18:06.553 --> 18:07.654
DO YOU MIND IF WE TALK LATER?

18:07.687 --> 18:11.324
- [sighs]
SURE. NO HURRY.

18:11.358 --> 18:13.626
WE'LL TALK WHEN YOU GET BACK.

18:16.763 --> 18:19.632
- THANK YOU, BABY.

18:19.666 --> 18:21.868
BYE, HONEY.
- BYE.

18:21.901 --> 18:25.205
- LUPE.

18:25.238 --> 18:27.907
[sing-song]
COME OUT, LUPE.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.509
[knock at door]

18:29.542 --> 18:32.379
COME IN.

18:32.412 --> 18:34.647
COME ON, PUSS. BE A GOOD PUSS.

18:34.681 --> 18:36.349
COME ON NOW.

18:36.383 --> 18:37.650
COME ON, PUSS-PUSS.

18:37.684 --> 18:39.219
- WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

18:39.252 --> 18:41.621
- LUPE. COME ON,
PUSS, PUSS, PUSS, PUSS.

18:41.654 --> 18:43.490
- YEAH, YOUR CLEANING LADY'S
NEVER GOING TO COME OUT

18:43.523 --> 18:44.824
IF YOU TALK TO HER LIKE THAT.

18:44.857 --> 18:46.759
- LUPE'S MY CAT.

18:46.793 --> 18:49.362
- YOU GOT A CAT?

18:49.396 --> 18:51.164
- YEAH, I THOUGHT IT'D BE NICE

18:51.198 --> 18:53.300
TO HAVE SOMETHING WARM
AND PURRING TO COME HOME TO.

18:53.333 --> 18:54.501
- HMM, AIN'T THAT THE TRUTH?

18:54.534 --> 18:55.568
- THE MINUTE I BROUGHT HER IN,

18:55.602 --> 18:57.270
SHE RAN STRAIGHT
FOR THE BEDROOM.

18:57.304 --> 18:59.172
- HMM, A FELINE
AFTER MY OWN HEART.

18:59.206 --> 19:00.840
- AND NOW SHE'S HIDING
IN THE CLOSET.

19:00.873 --> 19:03.443
- WELL, SHE'LL COME OUT
IN HER OWN TIME,

19:03.476 --> 19:05.678
JUST LIKE THE REST OF US.
MEANWHILE, COME.

19:05.712 --> 19:09.649
CONCENTRATE ON
MY CRASS CONSUMERISM.

19:09.682 --> 19:12.785
SPANDEX AS FAR
AS THE EYE CAN SEE,

19:12.819 --> 19:15.388
IN EVERY COLOR OF THE RAINBOW.

19:15.422 --> 19:18.791
A DIFFERENT ENSEMBLE FOR
EVERY DAY OF THE LIBERTY RIDE.

19:18.825 --> 19:20.327
- THAT'S VERY THOUGHTFUL
OF YOU, EM.

19:20.360 --> 19:21.661
NOT TO MENTION EXTRAVAGANT.

19:21.694 --> 19:22.662
BUT I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
I'M NOT GOING.

19:22.695 --> 19:24.331
- WHO SAID IT'S FOR YOU?

19:24.364 --> 19:25.698
- WHO ELSE?

19:25.732 --> 19:28.201
- ME. I DECIDED TO GO.

19:28.235 --> 19:29.936
- I THOUGHT YOU SAID YOU WERE
TOO BUSY WORKING.

19:29.969 --> 19:31.338
- WELL, THE BUSHES WILL
HAVE TO PLAN

19:31.371 --> 19:33.273
THEIR NEXT STATE DINNER
WITHOUT ME.

19:33.306 --> 19:34.941
- THAT YOU DIDN'T HAVE THE MONEY
FOR THE REGISTRATION FEE.

19:34.974 --> 19:38.545
- A VERY GOOD FRIEND
JUST PAID ME BACK.

19:38.578 --> 19:40.347
- THAT YOU WERE AFRAID OF
BEING EATEN BY A BEAR.

19:40.380 --> 19:44.817
- WELL, AT LEAST THE KIND THAT
LIVE IN THE WILDS OF CANADA.

19:44.851 --> 19:47.420
BUT I'M WILLING TO CONFRONT
MY DARKEST FEARS

19:47.454 --> 19:51.491
FOR A WORTHY CAUSE,
SUCH AS HELPING A FRIEND...

19:51.524 --> 19:52.959
BEING HIS SUPPORT SYSTEM,

19:52.992 --> 19:56.863
SEEING HIM THROUGH ANY CRISIS,
GREAT OR SMALL.

19:58.465 --> 20:00.967
- YOU'D REALLY DO THAT FOR ME?

20:01.000 --> 20:02.902
- I BELIEVE IN YOU, TEDDY.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.437
DESPITE EVERYTHING.

20:04.471 --> 20:09.376
I, UH, I WANT YOU TO SUCCEED.

20:09.409 --> 20:12.945
THINK I'LL SAVE THE TANGERINE
FOR THE FINISH LINE. HMM?

20:15.415 --> 20:18.518
[cheering]

20:18.551 --> 20:23.356
all: LIBERTY RIDE, LIBERTY RIDE,
GO, LIBERTY RIDE!

20:23.390 --> 20:24.791
[cheers and applause]

20:24.824 --> 20:27.527
- THE CENTER THANKS
EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU

20:27.560 --> 20:29.729
FOR PUTTING FORTH
THIS WONDERFUL EFFORT

20:29.762 --> 20:33.333
TO BENEFIT
LIBERTY HOUSE HOSPICE.

20:33.366 --> 20:37.003
- WE WISH YOU ALL
A GREAT JOURNEY UP TO TORONTO,

20:37.036 --> 20:39.372
AND A SAFE RIDE
BACK TO PITTSBURGH.

20:39.406 --> 20:40.940
MAY THIS BE THE ADVENTURE
OF A LIFETIME.

20:40.973 --> 20:45.412
[cheering]

20:45.445 --> 20:48.348
- PLEASE MAKE SURE
YOUR BIKES ARE ON THE TRUCK.

20:48.381 --> 20:49.816
- THERE YOU GO, HONEY.
IT'S SALAMI.

20:49.849 --> 20:51.751
I'M AFRAID WE'RE OUT OF TUNA.

20:51.784 --> 20:53.620
- THANK YOU.
- THERE YOU GO.

20:53.653 --> 20:56.356
I'M SO PROUD OF ALL OF YOU
FOR DOING THIS.

20:56.389 --> 20:57.890
THERE YOU GO, SWEETHEART.
- THANK YOU.

20:57.924 --> 20:59.058
- HERE, HONEY.
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

20:59.091 --> 21:02.795
- THANKS, DEB.
- HI, HONEY...

21:02.829 --> 21:04.831
- ALL SET.
LET'S GET ON BOARD.

21:04.864 --> 21:06.566
- I HAVEN'T BEEN ON A BUS
SINCE NINTH GRADE.

21:06.599 --> 21:08.901
GUYS WOULD BE GETTING BLOWJOBS
IN THE BACK.

21:08.935 --> 21:13.440
- AH, THE GOOD OLD DAYS
OF JUNIOR HIGH.

21:13.473 --> 21:17.043
- WELL, IF IT ISN'T PAPA BEAR
AND MAMA BEAR AND BABY BEAR.

21:17.076 --> 21:18.911
- BRIAN!

21:18.945 --> 21:20.913
- JUST THOUGHT I'D STOP BY TO
REMIND YOU TO WEAR YOUR HELMETS,

21:20.947 --> 21:22.515
STAY TO THE RIGHT,

21:22.549 --> 21:25.051
AND BE SURE TO
USE YOUR HAND GESTURES.

21:25.084 --> 21:26.653
- THANKS FOR ALL
THE MOTHERLY ADVICE,

21:26.686 --> 21:28.855
BUT MY MOTHER'S GOING WITH ME.

21:28.888 --> 21:31.391
I'M SORRY YOU'RE NOT.

21:31.424 --> 21:33.793
- HEY, HAVE A GREAT TRIP,
YOU GUYS.

21:33.826 --> 21:35.795
- MEL, WHAT A SURPRISE.

21:35.828 --> 21:37.930
I HEARD YOU'D BEEN SPENDING
MOST OF YOUR TIME IN BED.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.399
- LIVING THE LIFE OF BRIAN.

21:39.432 --> 21:40.700
- WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

21:40.733 --> 21:42.435
YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO--

21:42.469 --> 21:44.070
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR--
- NO, I'M NOT OUT OF MY...

21:44.103 --> 21:45.705
I JUST CAME DOWN TO SEE YOU
OFF, THAT'S ALL.

21:45.738 --> 21:48.441
SO STOP WORRYING.
I'M FINE.

21:48.475 --> 21:49.976
- JUST DON'T
LET MY MOM SEE YOU.

21:50.009 --> 21:51.578
YOU KNOW HOW HYSTERICAL
SHE GETS.

21:51.611 --> 21:54.714
- YOUR MOM? RIGHT.

21:54.747 --> 21:58.351
[indistinct chatter]

22:01.421 --> 22:03.923
- WE MADE JUST ENOUGH LUNCHES.

22:08.895 --> 22:12.098
I GUESS HE'S NOT COMING, HONEY.

22:12.131 --> 22:17.103
- I THOUGHT I'D CONVINCED HIM
TO CHANGE HIS MIND.

22:17.136 --> 22:20.473
- MICHAEL! GET YOUR ASSES
ON BOARD, YOU GUYS.

22:20.507 --> 22:23.943
COME ON.
AND SAVE ME A SEAT.

22:28.615 --> 22:32.485
COMING?

22:32.519 --> 22:35.888
[engine revs]
- DEBBIE!

22:35.922 --> 22:38.725
- CARL!

22:38.758 --> 22:40.026
SWEET OF YOU TO COME DOWN HERE.

22:40.059 --> 22:41.027
I TOLD YOU YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

22:41.060 --> 22:42.662
- YES, I DID.

22:42.695 --> 22:45.498
I COULDN'T LEAVE WITHOUT...
TELLING YOU...

22:45.532 --> 22:46.866
- MA, WOULD YOU GET ON THE BUS?

22:46.899 --> 22:48.635
- I GOTTA GO.

22:48.668 --> 22:51.037
I'LL CALL YOU WHEN I GET THERE.

22:51.070 --> 22:52.905
- CAN YOU WAIT A GODDAMN MINUTE?

22:52.939 --> 22:55.908
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO ASK YOU
FOR THE LAST TWO DAYS.

22:55.942 --> 22:58.511
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

22:58.545 --> 23:00.012
- WHAT?

23:00.046 --> 23:04.484
- I SAID, MARRY ME.

23:04.517 --> 23:07.820
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

23:18.565 --> 23:22.201
- TELL HIM YES,
AND GET ON THE BUS.

23:22.234 --> 23:25.037
- YES.

23:25.071 --> 23:27.039
YES.

23:27.073 --> 23:30.176
OF COURSE I'LL MARRY YOU.

23:30.209 --> 23:33.112
FUCK!

23:48.094 --> 23:50.697
[cheering]

23:56.235 --> 23:58.705
BYE.

24:03.142 --> 24:05.111
BYE.

24:10.983 --> 24:13.920
[cheers and applause]

24:17.023 --> 24:18.958
[indistinct chatter]

24:18.991 --> 24:20.226
- KEEP THE CHANGE.

24:20.259 --> 24:24.096
THANK YOU.

24:24.130 --> 24:28.568
SHIT! HEY.

24:28.601 --> 24:31.771
HEY!

24:31.804 --> 24:33.239
HEY!

24:33.272 --> 24:34.707
- STOP--STOP THE BUS!

24:34.741 --> 24:36.108
STOP THE FUCKING BUS!

24:36.142 --> 24:38.811
- HEY! HEY!
[horn honking]

24:47.787 --> 24:50.056
THANK YOU.

24:57.764 --> 25:01.601
MADE IT.
- KNEW YOU WOULD.

25:11.978 --> 25:15.815
- WHERE THE FUCK HAVE YOU BEEN?

25:15.848 --> 25:16.949
I COME HOME,
YOU'RE NOT HERE,

25:16.983 --> 25:18.685
I LOOK EVERYWHERE,
FRANTIC.

25:18.718 --> 25:20.286
I WAS ABOUT
TO CALL THE HOSPITAL,

25:20.319 --> 25:21.954
THE POLICE, THE MORGUE.

25:21.988 --> 25:24.023
I THOUGHT SOMETHING TERRIBLE
HAD HAPPENED.

25:24.056 --> 25:27.960
- WOULD YOU CALM DOWN?
- NO, I WILL NOT CALM DOWN.

25:27.994 --> 25:30.229
YOU SCARED THE SHIT OUT OF ME.

25:30.262 --> 25:33.165
- I'M SORRY.
- OH, I CAN TELL.

25:33.199 --> 25:35.935
- I WENT TO
THE LIBERTY RIDE SEND-OFF.

25:35.968 --> 25:38.104
- WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?

25:38.137 --> 25:41.107
AFTER EVERYONE TOLD YOU...

25:41.140 --> 25:42.308
TO SPITE ME?

25:42.341 --> 25:44.577
- [scoffs]

25:44.611 --> 25:46.312
THAT'S RIGHT, HONEY.

25:46.345 --> 25:49.315
MAKE IT ALL ABOUT YOU,
AS USUAL.

25:49.348 --> 25:52.184
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO HAS
A RIGHT TO BE ANGRY,

25:52.218 --> 25:55.187
TO BE INDIGNANT,
TO FEEL BETRAYED.

25:55.221 --> 25:56.956
WELL, GUESS WHAT,
MY SHIKSA GODDESS.

25:56.989 --> 25:58.825
- YOU DON'T CALL ME THAT.

25:58.858 --> 26:01.628
- THIS TIME IT ISN'T ABOUT YOU.

26:01.661 --> 26:03.062
IT'S ABOUT ME.

26:03.095 --> 26:05.698
I WENT OUT BECAUSE
IF I STAYED IN THIS HOUSE

26:05.732 --> 26:07.333
ANOTHER MINUTE WITH YOU,

26:07.366 --> 26:11.804
I'D GO OUT OF MY FUCKING MIND.

26:11.838 --> 26:13.940
SO I LEFT,
FOR TEN MINUTES.

26:13.973 --> 26:16.208
OKAY, 1/2 HOUR, TOPS.

26:16.242 --> 26:18.344
I DROVE OVER TO LIBERTY AVENUE,

26:18.377 --> 26:20.246
SAID MY GOOD-BYES,
AND DROVE BACK.

26:20.279 --> 26:22.348
AND LOOK. HERE I AM.

26:22.381 --> 26:25.885
MIRACLE OF MIRACLES,
ALIVE AND STILL IN ONE PIECE.

26:43.435 --> 26:46.973
- [sighs]

26:47.006 --> 26:50.743
WE CAN'T GO ON DOING
THE ALL-FEMALE VERSION

26:50.777 --> 26:55.748
OF WHO'S AFRAID
OF VIRGINIA WOOLF?

26:55.782 --> 27:00.987
IT'S JUST TOO EXHAUSTING.

27:01.020 --> 27:04.123
YOU CAN'T FORGIVE ME,

27:04.156 --> 27:07.259
NO MATTER HOW MUCH I APOLOGIZE

27:07.293 --> 27:10.396
AND TRY TO MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

27:10.429 --> 27:14.300
AND I'M STARTING
NOT TO CARE.

27:16.202 --> 27:17.904
I MEAN, AFTER ALL,
HOW MANY TIMES

27:17.937 --> 27:19.405
CAN SOMEONE REJECT YOU

27:19.438 --> 27:23.776
BEFORE YOU FINALLY
JUST GIVE UP?

27:26.478 --> 27:29.315
- SO WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

27:35.788 --> 27:39.759
- THAT PERHAPS IT'S BEST...

27:39.792 --> 27:42.328
FOR BOTH OF US...

27:42.361 --> 27:46.332
AND FOR GUS AND THE BABY...

27:49.235 --> 27:52.972
IF WE AREN'T TOGETHER.

27:55.942 --> 28:00.046
THAT WE STOP PUTTING EACH OTHER
THROUGH NEEDLESS HELL,

28:00.079 --> 28:04.450
TRYING TO REPAIR SOMETHING
WHICH OBVIOUSLY CAN'T BE FIXED.

28:04.483 --> 28:09.088
- I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:19.098 --> 28:24.904
- I'LL STAY
UNTIL AFTER THE BABY'S BORN.

28:29.275 --> 28:30.476
- HOW IS THE LUNCH?

28:30.509 --> 28:34.246
I MADE IT WITH
MY OWN TWO HANDS.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.883
HOW ABOUT THOSE LEMON BARS,
HUH?

28:36.916 --> 28:38.985
